  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "UonljBBmqqU4VX3A+IthNA/FamQ=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Operations have a clear primary/backup relationship across layers:\n\n| Data | PGlite | Swarm /bytes | Swarm feeds | IndexedDB |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Operations (raw) | PRIMARY | BACKUP | \u2014 | pending only |\n| Document state (computed) | DERIVED | not stored | \u2014 | \u2014 |\n| Doc/drive/user manifests | \u2014 | PAYLOAD | POINTER | \u2014 |\n| Signer key | \u2014 | \u2014 | \u2014 | cache only (re-derivable from wallet) |\n| Pending ops buffer | \u2014 | \u2014 | \u2014 | temporary (cleared after flush) |\n\nKey consequences:\n- **Document state is derived**, never stored on Swarm \u2014 always recomputed from operations on load.\n- **Manifests exist in both /bytes and feeds**: the /bytes chunk holds the payload, the feed holds the pointer to the latest version.\n- **The signer key is a cache only**, re-derivable from the wallet signature.\n- **Pending ops are temporary** \u2014 cleared once flushed to Swarm.\n\nThis split is intentional: PGlite optimizes hot reads, Swarm optimizes durability, manifests use the feed-as-pointer pattern to make \"latest version\" lookups cheap.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
    }
  },
